# isEqual:

**Article**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver and a given object have identical URL strings and base URLs.

## Overview

This method defines what it means for instances to be equal. Two NSURLs are considered equal if and only if they return identical values for both [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSURL/baseURL] and [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSURL/relativeString].
